Interface RoutingLogic

All Superinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
AdaptiveLoadBalancingRoutingLogic, BalancingRoutingLogic, BroadcastRoutingLogic, ConsistentHashingRoutingLogic, RandomRoutingLogic, RoundRobinRoutingLogic, ScatterGatherFirstCompletedRoutingLogic, SmallestMailboxRoutingLogic, TailChoppingRoutingLogic
public interface RoutingLogic
extends NoSerializationVerificationNeeded

The interface of the routing logic that is used in a Router to select destination routed messages.

The implementation must be thread safe.

Method Detail

select

Routee select(java.lang.Object message,
              scala.collection.immutable.IndexedSeq<Routee> routees)
Pick the destination for a given message. Normally it picks one of the passed routees, but in the end it is up to the implementation to return whatever Routee to use for sending a specific message.

When implemented from Java it can be good to know that routees.apply(index) can be used to get an element from the IndexedSeq.
